haps 50%. I don't think compulsory insurance would work/ be enforceable but this might help</span><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><br /><br /><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">coi</span><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> - cyclist - recently knocked off my bicycle by blithering idiot. I was behaving 'perfectly'. 2nd serious accident in 4 years, neither avoidable.</span><br /><br /><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am insured and member of CTC.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="color:#333366; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>